						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in a field towards the south of the village.</p>						

						<p>Harihara II, 1401 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1325, Vṛisha, Pushya ba. 6, Monday, Saṁkramaṇa.</hi> The Śaka and the cyclic years do not agree. If Śaka 1325 is a mistake for 1323 which corresponds with Vṛisha, the details regularly correspond to <hi rend="bold">1401 A.D., December 26, Monday, ·82.</hi> The date falls in the reign of Harihara II.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of some <hi rend="italic">vṛittis</hi> in the village Śivapuram by a nāyaka (name not clear) son of Pemmi-nāyaka, to Mallu-bhaṭṭa for worship and offerings to god Mallinātha for the merit of his parents when <hi rend="bold">Komāra Harihararāya,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Vīra Virūparāya</hi> was ruling in Rāyavaram.</p>						

						</summary>
